explanations.description: The token often refers to an object or a concept, particularly in phrases or idioms, such as "straw" in "straw man", "drawing straws", or "grasping at straws", but also appears as a literal object, like straw or hay, in various contexts, including agriculture, food, or crafts, and sometimes as part of a metaphorical or poetic expression.
